Create docker having jenkins in port 8070
To run Jenkins in Docker on port 8070, you just need to map your local port to Jenkins container port 8080.
✅ Run Jenkins container on port 8070

Execute this in Ubuntu (WSL) or PowerShell:

docker run -d \
  --name jenkins \
  -p 8070:8080 \
  -p 50000:50000 \
  jenkins/jenkins:lts
🧠 What this means
Part	Meaning
8070:8080	Your PC port 8070 → Jenkins inside container port 8080
50000:50000	Jenkins agent communication
jenkins/jenkins:lts	Official Jenkins image
🌐 Access Jenkins

After it starts, open:

http://localhost:8070
🔑 Get Jenkins initial password

Run:

docker exec -it jenkins cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword

Copy the password and paste into browser.

⚠️ If port already used

Check:

netstat -ano | findstr 8070

or change port:

-p 8085:8080
🚀 Optional (recommended for persistence)

So Jenkins data is not lost:

docker run -d \
  --name jenkins \
  -p 8070:8080 \
  -p 50000:50000 \
  -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home \
  jenkins/jenkins:lts

Port 50000 is used by Jenkins for agent (slave) communication.

🧠 What port 50000 is for

When you run Jenkins in Docker:

Jenkins Controller (Master)
        │
        │  TCP 50000
        ▼
Jenkins Agents (Workers)

So:

8080 / 8070 → Web UI (you open in browser)
50000 → Jenkins agents connect to Jenkins server
🤖 Why Jenkins needs it

It is used when you:

Run builds on another machine/container
Use distributed builds
Connect Jenkins agents via JNLP (Java Web Start protocol)
❗ Do you always need port 50000?

👉 No

If you are:

Only using Jenkins locally
Not adding agents

You can safely remove it.

✅ Option 1 (simple — recommended for you)
docker run -d \
  --name jenkins \
  -p 8070:8080 \
  jenkins/jenkins:lts

✔ Works fine for learning
✔ Web UI only
❌ No agent connections (not needed yet)

✅ Option 2 (full setup)

If you want full Jenkins architecture:

docker run -d \
  --name jenkins \
  -p 8070:8080 \
  -p 50000:50000 \
  jenkins/jenkins:lts
🚀 Recommendation

Since you're just starting Jenkins:

👉 Use only port 8070
👉 Ignore 50000 for now

